      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAYDOWNLILY (5) has been right there in all four runs this preparation and is a three-time winner over this track and trip. Ready to peak now and should be right there at the business end. KING YOSHI (1) loves racing at this circuit with seven wins and four placings from 13 attempts. Should be able to sit up on speed and will give backers a sight. KING SPIRIT (6) goes well for hoop Tierney who has two wins and a placing from just three steers and again gets the benefit of her 3kg claim. Has to be included in calculations. CAMPAI (3) is knocking on the door of another victory with three consecutive runner-up finishes. A must for the multiples. The well-related NEVER SAY NAY (7) (half to G1 winner Hayasugi) best of the rest.",
